# Reindex Search After Content Changes

When creating, modifying, or deleting markdown files in `src/content/` OR modifying category definitions in `src/data/categories.ts`, you MUST reindex the Upstash search index.

According to `SEARCH_IMPLEMENTATION.md`: "Whenever markdown content changes (`src/content/**`) or category titles are updated (`src/data/categories.ts`), reindex."

## Required Action

After any content change (create, edit, delete), run:

```bash
pnpm run index:search
```

## When to Reindex

- ✅ Creating a new article (`src/content/{lang}/{category}/*.md`)
- ✅ Modifying existing article content
- ✅ Updating article frontmatter (title, excerpt)
- ✅ Deleting articles
- ✅ Modifying category definitions (`src/data/categories.ts`)

## Verification

After reindexing, verify (as per `SEARCH_IMPLEMENTATION.md`):
1. Command completes successfully with expected output:
   - `Upserted ... / ... documents`
   - `Search indexing finished successfully.`
2. Document count matches expected number
3. Test search functionality in the UI:
   - Run `pnpm dev`
   - Open `/en/`, `/id/`, `/th/`
   - Search a known term from each locale
   - Confirm relevant results appear

## Important Notes

- The indexing script reads from `src/content/{en,id,th}/` directories
- Environment variables (`UPSTASH_SEARCH_REST_URL`, `UPSTASH_SEARCH_REST_TOKEN`) must be set in `.env`
- The script automatically handles markdown stripping and content truncation
